snippet.textDisplay:
I was really enjoying watching Joey again and doing this cat vlogs. Up until the birth.
I have fostered and raised many cat family (mother and kittens) and first rule is do not interrupt the birth (dont be shoving your hands and face and CAMERA in her face!) and especially DO NOT touch the babies!
I understand he might think he knows what he’s doing from having puppies before. But kittens are NOTHING a like. They do their own thing and are a LOT happier letting them do what they need to do.
Touching the kittens AT ALL that age can remove her scent and make the kittens smell like you which then the mother cat can reject and actually KILL her babies!

PLEASE DO MORE RESEARCH WHEN LOOKING AFTER LIVING THINGS! THIS VIDEO WAS SO UNSETTLING AND ALMOST GROSS TO WATCH.

snippet.textDisplay:
I had kittens few times and best tip I have for you is - don’t touch them. There’s a possibility you leave your scent on them and other kittens, maybe even mum, doesn’t recognise them as part of her family which can be lethal... I’ve seen it happening 😔😔
Let them all be together, make sure mum is okey, give her water, food and leave litter close to where they are. She’ll take care of them. It might look like she doesn’t care but she’s an animal and has instincts - she’ll try to hide them from you if she thinks you’re too close. When they open their eyes (which should happen in 10-14 days) that’s the time to let them get to know you. Of course you can come and watch them, there should be enough food for all of them but if you see that one of them isn’t growing (they grow super fast), call a vet.
